    <h4 style="padding-top:80px;" id="intro">Introduction</h4>
    <p>
        Welcome to our e-Nompilo privacy and security page. We are committed to protecting
        your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines
        how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your personal data in connection with our vaccination
        services. By using our services, you consent to the practices described in this policy.
    </p>

    <h4 style="padding-top:80px;" id="2">Data Collection</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>We collect personal and medical information necessary for healthcare purposes.</li>
        <li>
            Data collected may include:
            <ul>
                <li>Personal details (name, contact information)</li>
                <li>Medical history</li>
                <li>Vaccination dates and records</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Your data is collected solely for the purpose of administering and providing healthcare services.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="padding-top:80px;" id="3">How we use your information</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Scheduling and administering appointments</li>
        <li>Verifying your identity and eligibility for medical facilities</li>
        <li>Communicating with you about your appointments and follow-up care</li>
        <li>Reporting and complying with public health requirements</li>
        <li>Improving our services and customer experience</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="padding-top:80px;" id="4">Children's privacy</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Some of our services are intended for use of people over the age of 15</li>
        <li>We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under this age without parental consent.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="padding-top:80px;" id="5">Data Security</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Your data is secured using state-of-the-art encryption methods.</li>
        <li>Access to your data is strictly controlled, and only authorized personnel have access.</li>
        <li>Regular security audits and assessments are conducted to ensure the highest level of protection.</li>
        <li>We comply with all relevant data security standards and regulations (e.g., HIPAA).</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="padding-top:80px;" id="6">Data Privacy</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>We treat your data with the utmost confidentiality.</li>
        <li>Informed consent is obtained for data collection, and you have control over your data.</li>
        <li>We do not share your data with third parties without your explicit consent, except as required by law.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="padding-top:80px;" id="7">Access and Control</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>You have the right to access, review, and update your personal information.</li>
        <li>You can request the removal of your data from our system at any time.</li>
        <li>Manage your privacy preferences through our user-friendly tools.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="padding-top:80px;" id="8">Third-Party Involvement</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>We may collaborate with trusted third-party vendors or partners to enhance our services.</li>
        <li>These partners are also committed to data security and privacy best practices.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="padding-top:80px;" id="9">Data Retention</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>We retain data only as long as necessary for vaccination and healthcare purposes.</li>
        <li>Data is securely deleted when no longer needed.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="padding-top:80px;" id="10">Incident Response</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Rigorous procedures are in place to respond to data breaches or security incidents.</li>
        <li>We will notify affected individuals and relevant authorities as required by law.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="padding-top:80px;" id="11">Compliance</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>We are fully compliant with data protection regulations and standards applicable to our region or user base.</li>
    </ul>

